desmoj.extensions.applicationDomains.harbour

Class FIFO_Transport_Strategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • desmoj.core.simulator.NamedObject
      • desmoj.core.simulator.ModelComponent
        • desmoj.extensions.applicationDomains.harbour.FIFO_Transport_Strategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransportStrategy

    public class FIFO_Transport_Strategy
extends ModelComponent
implements TransportStrategy
    The FIFO_Transport_Strategy is the strategy that a transporter control uses by the assigning of the jobs to transporters the following way: the first Job in the queue of jobs is assigned to the first transporter in the queue of transportes. The FIFO_Transport_Strategy implements the method getJobs (ProcessQueue Transporter, Queue Jobs) of the TransportStategy. The FIFO_Transport_Strategy is derived from ModelComponent.
    See Also:
    TransportStrategy, TransporterJob, T_Control, ModelComponent

    • Method Detail

      • getJobs

        public TransporterJob[] getJobs(ProcessQueue transporters,
                                Queue jobs)
        This method describes the following way of the assigning the jobs to transporters: the first job in the queue of the jobs will be assigned to the first transporter in the queue of the transpoters, this each assignment will be stored in a TranspoterJob. All the assignments are used by the transport control.
        Specified by:
        getJobs in interface TransportStrategy
        Parameters:
        Jobs - Queue: The queue with the jobs of the transporter control.
        Returns:
        TransporterJob[] : The pairs of the transporters with the their assigned jobs.
